nodes.bodyText:
Like in the comment, it is needed to:
// Verify the replicated entry corresponds to the current log entry sync cycle (and not a previous/old one)
The first time we enter LOG_ENTRY_SYNC it is random (because we need an initial one) after that ACKs are always stamped with the same one. It allows to discard an event originated by an old replication cycle, which is not the current one.

